text:
Join us for the Semi-Finals of the Hot Wheels Legends Tour! Watch LIVE judging from a panel of celebrities and top motorsport athletes, including Coco Zurita, Aimee Shackelford, and Eric Kendricks
The Hot Wheels Legends Tour, now in its sixth year, is a global search for the next fan-made custom car to be made into a Hot Wheels die-cast.

The Hot Wheels Legends Tour is made possible in partnership with Walmart and Presenting Sponsor, Mobil 1.
Learn more about the Hot Wheels Legends Tour at www.hotwheels.com/legends

From jaw-dropping custom cars to the hottest rides in town, the show was nothing short of impressive. The range of vehicles on display was downright stunning, with mini trucks, prototypes, hot rods, and everything in between taking the stage.

The epic day culminated as we crowned Wayne Dick and his build ‚ÄúRampy‚Äù as the El Segundo Hot Wheels Legends Tour finalist. üöóüí®üèÜ

ARTFUL RELICS

Aged, eroded, but ultimately unbroken. Our Hot Wheels x Daniel Arsham collab begins with the decayed Super Rally Case featuring a frosted back and rubble-inspired shelves. Start filling it with the 1:64 version of Arsham‚Äôs Porsche 930 sculpture and the Eroded Rodger Dodger.

"To give the vehicles a premium feel, we turned to Silkstone, a modern material that has a porcelain appearance and a heavier, more tactile feel than plastic. It allows for more sharpness and details than die-cast metal." - Ethan Wood, Senior Director of Design

Get these Mattel Creations collectibles on October 27 at MattelCreations.com at 9 AM PT or IRL October 21-October 22 at our Hot Wheels x Daniel Arsham NYC Celebration.

Rough and ready.üèî

Covered in green-cyan with Real Riders off-road wheels and light smoke-tinted windows, the Elite 64 Land Rover Defender 90 Pickup is a collectors dream car.

Meet Rampy, the latest finalist on the Hot Wheels Legends Tour. Built by the automotive virtuoso Wayne Dick! üöóüí® It took 2 years and a whopping 790 hours of fabrication to create this automotive masterpiece. With a 6.2L engine, BTR stage 3 cam, and 420HP on the wheels, it's pure power on four wheels. Featuring C5 suspension, Air Rex struts, Acuair air management system, and Weld wheels, this ride is a work of art on wheels. üõ†Ô∏è

Starting as a bone-stock truck, it's been transformed into a speed demon with heart and soul. Rampy's journey includes an 11.89-second quarter-mile run at 110mph, conquering autocross, and cruising 20k miles in just 18 months.

But Rampy's true mission? To drive, have fun, and bring smiles to people's faces everywhere it goes. ü§©üôå Congratulations to Wayne and Rampy on taking the El Segundo Hot Wheels Legends Tour finalist spot!
